00:54:21,650 --> 00:54:24,141
I reckon y'all need glasses.

498
00:54:35,163 --> 00:54:37,321
Now, hold still.

499
00:54:38,332 --> 00:54:40,455
Want some more cookies?

500
00:54:40,876 --> 00:54:43,581
- More milk?
- I'm full.

501
00:54:53,471 --> 00:54:55,879
How come you've stayed with the coach?

502
00:54:56,099 --> 00:54:57,807
You don't like him much.

503
00:54:58,059 --> 00:55:00,550
I wasn't brought up to leave a husband.

504
00:55:00,770 --> 00:55:02,561
I guess that's why.

505
00:55:02,897 --> 00:55:05,055
Maybe I was just scared to.

506
00:55:06,150 --> 00:55:09,104
I never noticed how ugly this room is.

507
00:55:09,319 --> 00:55:11,111
What's your favourite colour?

508
00:55:11,321 --> 00:55:12,566
I don't know. Blue.

509
00:55:12,781 --> 00:55:15,698
- Maybe I'll repaper it.
- Why'd you marry him?

510
00:55:15,951 --> 00:55:18,239
I don't know.
My mother didn't like him.

511
00:55:18,453 --> 00:55:20,077
Maybe that was it.

512
00:55:20,747 --> 00:55:22,454
Well, I was 20 years old.

513
00:55:22,707 --> 00:55:26,751
I thought hairy-chested
football coaches were about it.

514
00:55:27,086 --> 00:55:29,624
I'm gonna buy us a new quilt.

515
00:55:30,047 --> 00:55:31,375
A blue one.

516
00:55:32,883 --> 00:55:35,374
What you think he'd do if he found us?

517
00:55:35,594 --> 00:55:37,385
Shoot us, probably.

518
00:55:37,971 --> 00:55:41,340
He's always glad to have an excuse
to use his deer rifle.

519
00:55:58,991 --> 00:56:03,652
I thought you boys wanted to fish.
Keep an eye on them corks, Billy.

520
00:56:09,584 --> 00:56:12,538
I don't think there's anything
here except turtles.

521
00:56:12,753 --> 00:56:15,624
That's what I like about it, tell you the truth.

522
00:56:15,840 --> 00:56:18,046
- Want to try one?
- Sure.

523
00:56:21,178 --> 00:56:24,095
I never liked to clean fish or eat them either.

524
00:56:24,306 --> 00:56:26,975
You spend half your time picking out bone.

525
00:56:29,477 --> 00:56:32,098
I just come out here to get a little scenery.

526
00:56:32,313 --> 00:56:34,721
Too pretty a day to spend in town.

527
00:56:38,819 --> 00:56:41,939
You wouldn't believe
how this country's changed.

528
00:56:45,242 --> 00:56:48,693
First time I seen it,
there wasn't a mesquite tree on it.

529
00:56:48,954 --> 00:56:50,946
Or a prickly pear neither.

530
00:56:51,456 --> 00:56:53,614
I used to own this land, you know.

531
00:56:55,168 --> 00:56:57,741
First time I watered a horse at this tank...

532
00:56:58,004 --> 00:57:00,210
...was more than 40 years ago.

533
00:57:02,174 --> 00:57:04,712
I reckon the reason I drag you out here is...

534
00:57:04,969 --> 00:57:09,132
...I'm as sentimental as the next
fellow when it comes to old times.

535
00:57:13,894 --> 00:57:15,471
Old times.

536
00:57:16,229 --> 00:57:19,146
I brought a young lady swimming out here once...

537
00:57:19,440 --> 00:57:21,433
...more than 20 years ago.

538
00:57:24,487 --> 00:57:27,441
It was after my wife had lost her mind.

539
00:57:27,698 --> 00:57:29,358
And my boys was dead.

540
00:57:32,870 --> 00:57:36,570
Me and this young lady was pretty wild, I guess.

541
00:57:37,541 --> 00:57:39,332
In pretty deep.

542
00:57:42,337 --> 00:57:46,548
We used to come here on horseback
and swim without no bathing suits.

543
00:57:49,719 --> 00:57:53,502
One day she wanted to swim
the horses across this tank.

544
00:57:53,764 --> 00:57:57,014
Kind of a crazy thing to do,
but we done it anyway.

545
00:57:58,018 --> 00:58:01,351
She bet me a silver dollar
she could beat me across.

546
00:58:02,314 --> 00:58:03,772
She did.

547
00:58:05,275 --> 00:58:08,644
This old horse I was riding
didn't want to take the water.

548
00:58:08,861 --> 00:58:12,526
But she was always looking
for something to do like that.

549
00:58:13,741 --> 00:58:15,449
Something wild.

550
00:58:17,578 --> 00:58:20,662
I bet she's still got that silver dollar.

551
00:58:23,333 --> 00:58:25,041
Whatever happened to her?

552
00:58:26,586 --> 00:58:28,294
She growed up.

553
00:58:29,339 --> 00:58:31,545
She was just a girl then, really.

554
00:58:34,052 --> 00:58:35,878
Let me help you with that.

555
00:58:37,221 --> 00:58:40,257
Why didn't you ever marry her
after your wife died?

556
00:58:42,601 --> 00:58:44,428
She was already married.

557
00:58:49,775 --> 00:58:53,108
Her and her husband was young
and miserable with one another...

558
00:58:53,320 --> 00:58:55,561
...like so many young married folks are.

559
00:58:56,281 --> 00:58:59,032
I thought they'd change with some age...

560
00:58:59,409 --> 00:59:01,318
...but it didn't turn out that way.

561
00:59:01,536 --> 00:59:04,323
- Is being married always so miserable?
- Not really.

562
00:59:04,830 --> 00:59:07,238
About 80 percent of the time, I guess.

563
00:59:09,960 --> 00:59:13,210
We ought to go to
a real fishing tank next year.

564
00:59:13,463 --> 00:59:16,832
It don't do to think
about things like that too much.

565
00:59:18,760 --> 00:59:21,677
If she was here,
I'd probably be just as crazy now...

566
00:59:21,930 --> 00:59:24,716
...as I was then in about five minutes.

567
00:59:25,349 --> 00:59:27,093
Ain't that ridiculous?

568
00:59:29,478 --> 00:59:31,435
No, it ain't really.

569
00:59:31,689 --> 00:59:35,900
Being crazy about a woman like her
is always the right thing to do.

570
00:59:37,903 --> 00:59:41,568
Being a decrepit old bag of bones,
that's what's ridiculous.

571
00:59:41,948 --> 00:59:43,526
Getting old.

572
01:00:35,665 --> 01:00:37,492
I'm glad I wasn't on fire.

573
01:00:37,750 --> 01:00:41,083
I'd have burned to death
before you got one button undone.

574
01:00:41,295 --> 01:00:43,501
I'm going to get a drink of water.

575
01:00:51,388 --> 01:00:54,721
I wondered where you went.
Annie-Annie asleep?

576
01:00:55,058 --> 01:00:56,433
Yeah.

577
01:01:11,448 --> 01:01:12,479
Nice.

578
01:01:12,699 --> 01:01:13,944
You a virgin?

579
01:01:15,327 --> 01:01:16,702
Guess I am.

580
01:01:17,913 --> 01:01:18,944
Too bad.

581
01:01:20,457 --> 01:01:23,291
- I don't want to be, though.
- I don't blame you.

582
01:01:24,002 --> 01:01:25,745
Come see me when you're not.

583
01:01:50,651 --> 01:01:54,400
Why don't we just go someplace?
I'm sick and tired of this town.

584
01:01:54,613 --> 01:01:56,855
- You're my only friend.
- Go and stay gone?

585
01:01:57,074 --> 01:01:59,197
Except Jacy. No, I don't know.

586
01:02:00,369 --> 01:02:03,204
Hey, we go to Mexico.
Be back sometime Monday.

587
01:02:03,413 --> 01:02:06,663
- Would the pickup make it?
- Yeah. How much money you got?

588
01:02:06,875 --> 01:02:08,037
Thirty bucks, about.

589
01:02:08,293 --> 01:02:11,044
Well, I got 40.
We can make it on that. Come on!

590
01:02:13,172 --> 01:02:14,370
You guys want...

591
01:02:14,966 --> 01:02:16,923
- Where you going?
- Mexico.

592
01:02:17,134 --> 01:02:18,083
Where?

593
01:02:24,766 --> 01:02:28,182
Better come with us, Sam.
We're headed for the valley.

594
01:02:28,562 --> 01:02:30,353
- Where did you say?
- Mexico.

595
01:02:30,563 --> 01:02:32,852
- It's about the wildest.
- All the way down.

596
01:02:33,483 --> 01:02:37,480
You going all the way to Mexico
tonight in this old heap of junk?

597
01:02:37,737 --> 01:02:38,982
My God!

598
01:02:39,238 --> 01:02:42,358
Reckon the town will get along
without us till Monday?

599
01:02:42,575 --> 01:02:43,570
I reckon.

600
01:02:43,784 --> 01:02:46,536
If I was young enough, I'd go with you.

601
01:02:46,912 --> 01:02:49,237
- Need any money?
- No, we got plenty.

602
01:02:49,957 --> 01:02:53,491
Well, you'd better take some
for some insurance.

603
01:02:54,169 --> 01:02:57,419
Take money below that border,
it sort of melts sometimes.

604
01:02:57,630 --> 01:02:58,911
Thanks, Sam.

605
01:02:59,716 --> 01:03:02,467
Try not to drink too much of that buggy water.

606
01:03:02,677 --> 01:03:05,512
We'll just drink beer and tequila.

607
01:03:06,305 --> 01:03:10,089
You catch the clap, you'll wish
you hadn't drunk nothing.

608
01:03:22,570 --> 01:03:23,768
Oh, well.

609
01:03:24,489 --> 01:03:25,651
We'll see you.

610
01:03:25,907 --> 01:03:27,615
- Thank you.
- So long.

611
01:03:59,146 --> 01:04:00,557
Hey, wake up!

612
01:04:00,939 --> 01:04:02,054
We're back.

613
01:04:04,067 --> 01:04:06,985
My stomach don't feel so good.
Got any more Tums?

614
01:04:07,529 --> 01:04:10,944
You ate them all
before we got to San Antonio.

615
01:04:12,200 --> 01:04:15,782
Genevieve will have something.
My stomach don't feel so good.

616
01:04:18,581 --> 01:04:19,576
Closed.

617
01:04:20,166 --> 01:04:21,624
Closed?

618
01:04:23,710 --> 01:04:25,869
I ain't never seen her closed before.

619
01:04:26,088 --> 01:04:28,164
No, not even for Christmas.

620
01:04:29,633 --> 01:04:33,048
Maybe Sam will have something.
I'm sick.

621
01:04:55,782 --> 01:04:57,525
Well, it ain't that early.

622
01:04:58,159 --> 01:04:59,867
Must be some kind of holiday.

623
01:05:00,119 --> 01:05:02,361
Sam don't close on holidays.

624
01:05:02,622 --> 01:05:04,947
Maybe he had to go someplace.

625
01:05:08,627 --> 01:05:10,536
Let's go ask Andy.

626
01:05:24,100 --> 01:05:27,184
- Somebody will steal the town.
- Where is everybody?

627
01:05:27,394 --> 01:05:31,392
- Asleep. Everybody that's got sense.
- Why'd Sam close the café?

628
01:05:32,024 --> 01:05:34,693
Oh, yeah. Y'all been gone, ain't you?

629
01:05:34,943 --> 01:05:36,603
Gone to Mexico.

630
01:05:37,028 --> 01:05:39,068
- You don't know about it.
- What?

631
01:05:39,280 --> 01:05:40,940
Sam died yesterday morning.

632
01:05:42,867 --> 01:05:43,898
Died?

633
01:05:44,118 --> 01:05:45,778
Yep. Quite a blow.

634
01:05:46,037 --> 01:05:49,655
Keeled over one of
the snooker tables, had a stroke.

635
01:05:50,583 --> 01:05:52,409
Sam the Lion?

636
01:05:52,793 --> 01:05:54,750
Yep. Sam's dead.

637
01:05:55,045 --> 01:05:56,788
He was quite a fellow.

638
01:05:58,840 --> 01:06:02,007
He had his own way of doing things,
that's for sure.

639
01:06:03,553 --> 01:06:07,004
They found his will.
Craziest thing you ever heard.

640
01:06:07,265 --> 01:06:11,179
He left you the pool hall, Sonny.
What do you think about that?

641
01:06:12,812 --> 01:06:14,970
He left Genevieve the café.

642
01:06:15,189 --> 01:06:18,273
That's the only thing he done
that made any sense.

643
01:06:18,734 --> 01:06:21,403
Left the picture show to old Miss Mosey.

644
01:06:21,653 --> 01:06:25,236
Hell, she's too far gone
to even run a popcorn machine.

645
01:06:25,782 --> 01:06:27,691
And the craziest thing of all...

646
01:06:27,909 --> 01:06:31,907
...he left $1000 to Joe Bob Blanton,
the preacher's boy.

647
01:06:32,455 --> 01:06:34,697
Beats all I ever heard of.

648
01:06:35,082 --> 01:06:37,704
He could just as easily left that to me.

649
01:06:37,918 --> 01:06:41,619
I deserve it at least as much
as that ignorant little bastard.

650
01:06:43,132 --> 01:06:45,171
Anyhow, it's done.

651
01:06:45,425 --> 01:06:47,465
They're burying him tomorrow.

652
01:09:09,226 --> 01:09:10,424
Come in.

653
01:09:25,616 --> 01:09:27,822
- I love you.
- I love you too.

654
01:09:59,147 --> 01:10:00,689
Oh, Duane, hurry.

655
01:10:35,973 --> 01:10:37,302
What's wrong, honey?

656
01:10:39,268 --> 01:10:40,810
I don't know.

657
01:10:42,396 --> 01:10:44,851
That tickles.
I can't stand to be tickled.

658
01:10:54,240 --> 01:10:56,945
What's the matter?
Aren't you gonna do it?

659
01:10:57,285 --> 01:10:58,660
I don't know what's wrong.

660
01:10:58,870 --> 01:11:02,488
How could anything be wrong?
Just go on and do it.

661
01:11:06,335 --> 01:11:08,126
What's the matter with you?

662
01:11:08,879 --> 01:11:10,871
I don't know, something's happened.

663
01:11:11,089 --> 01:11:14,043
Get off a minute!
You might fall and mash me.

664
01:11:14,259 --> 01:11:15,883
I don't know what happened.

665
01:11:16,094 --> 01:11:18,881
It was Mexico.
No telling what you got down there.

666
01:11:19,097 --> 01:11:21,469
I hate you!
I don't know why I dated you.

667
01:11:21,683 --> 01:11:23,640
I don't know what happened.

668
01:11:25,102 --> 01:11:28,970
Put your clothes on.
You think I want to look at you naked?

669
01:11:31,066 --> 01:11:33,853
I knew you couldn't do it.
I'll always be a virgin!

670
01:11:34,069 --> 01:11:36,145
What do we say?
The whole class knows.

671
01:11:36,363 --> 01:11:38,818
I want to cry.
You're the meanest boy ever.

672
01:11:39,032 --> 01:11:41,238
My mother was dead-right about you.

673
01:11:42,160 --> 01:11:43,654
I don't know what happened.

674
01:11:43,870 --> 01:11:46,824
Don't go out there!
We haven't had time to do it.

675
01:11:47,040 --> 01:11:49,791
I don't want anyone to know.
You better not tell.

676
01:11:51,002 --> 01:11:53,041
You just pretend it was wonderful!

677
01:11:53,254 --> 01:11:55,709
I'm sorry, I don't know what happened.

678
01:11:56,673 --> 01:11:58,749
If you say that again, I'll bite you!

679
01:12:19,111 --> 01:12:21,353
Tell us about it. What was it like?

680
01:12:24,449 --> 01:12:26,857
I just can't describe it.

681
01:12:27,244 --> 01:12:29,817
I just can't describe it in words.

682
01:13:14,746 --> 01:13:17,071
I can do it now. I know I can.

683
01:13:51,656 --> 01:13:54,905
Quit prissing! I don't think
you did it right anyway.

684
01:14:05,377 --> 01:14:06,539
Come on.

685
01:14:16,804 --> 01:14:20,137
It's your graduation present.
Hope you like it.

686
01:14:30,025 --> 01:14:32,183
I never seen one as nice.

687
01:14:45,080 --> 01:14:46,872
- Hello?
- Jacy?

688
01:14:47,082 --> 01:14:48,742
What's on your feeble mind?

689
01:14:48,959 --> 01:14:50,702
Same as been. I want a date.

690
01:14:51,837 --> 01:14:53,995
Why don't you just go back to Mexico?

691
01:14:54,214 --> 01:14:56,586
I guess girls are easier to please there.

692
01:14:57,008 --> 01:14:58,835
Just go with me one more time.

693
01:14:59,052 --> 01:15:00,546
You can at least see me.

694
01:15:00,762 --> 01:15:03,217
Pester someone else. I got a new boyfriend.

695
01:15:03,431 --> 01:15:05,470
- I can't be talking to you.
- Who?

696
01:15:05,683 --> 01:15:07,260
Bobby Sheen, of course.

697
01:15:09,144 --> 01:15:10,852
- You crazy?
- I certainly am not.

698
01:15:11,063 --> 01:15:14,763
I guess I wanted to go with him
all along and never realized it.

699
01:15:15,067 --> 01:15:17,604
Maybe we'll see you in Wichita sometime.

700
01:15:32,124 --> 01:15:35,041
Goddamn it! Goddamn it to hell!

701
01:15:47,305 --> 01:15:48,680
I hate to see you go.

702
01:15:48,931 --> 01:15:51,173
I don't got a goddamn thing to stay for.

703
01:15:51,392 --> 01:15:54,393
Roughnecks say you can get a job
in Odessa anytime.

704
01:15:55,104 --> 01:15:56,895
Come on back if you don't.

705
01:16:10,201 --> 01:16:12,443
You hear they busted up, let me know.

706
01:16:40,855 --> 01:16:43,393
Why don't we watch the movie?

707
01:16:47,903 --> 01:16:49,646
Hi, I didn't hear you.

708
01:16:50,113 --> 01:16:51,109
Gene home?

709
01:16:51,698 --> 01:16:54,023
No, he and Mama went to the club.

710
01:16:59,205 --> 01:17:01,743
What are you doing home on a Saturday night?

711
01:17:03,334 --> 01:17:05,706
Bobby Sheen ran off and got married.

712
01:17:08,505 --> 01:17:10,048
Annie-Annie Martin.

713
01:17:14,052 --> 01:17:16,009
Want me to turn the TV off?

714
01:17:16,221 --> 01:17:19,969
No, I'm gonna go play pool.
Tell your dad the well came in okay.

715
01:17:21,142 --> 01:17:24,428
I wish I could go to the pool hall.
I've always wanted to.

716
01:17:24,645 --> 01:17:27,599
It's terrible, the things
girls aren't allowed to do.

717
01:17:29,442 --> 01:17:32,526
Well, hell, come on.
I'll show you the pool hall.

718
01:17:32,736 --> 01:17:34,017
Aren't people there?

719
01:17:34,238 --> 01:17:36,942
If there are, they'll be in back asleep now.

720
01:17:37,157 --> 01:17:40,241
Won't bother us. I got my own key.

721
01:17:41,495 --> 01:17:43,368
Okay, I will then.

722
01:17:59,344 --> 01:18:01,918
Goodness, it sure is dark in here.

723
01:21:02,640 --> 01:21:06,340
What a night. I never thought
something like this would happen.

724
01:21:08,229 --> 01:21:10,055
How about hopping out?

725
01:21:45,305 --> 01:21:48,009
He's just awful!
Why do you fool with him?

726
01:21:48,224 --> 01:21:51,011
- Daddy's nicer than him, isn't he?
- He sure is.

727
01:21:51,227 --> 01:21:53,184
Your daddy's a very nice man.

728
01:21:53,396 --> 01:21:56,065
I ought to give Abilene hell instead of him.

729
01:21:56,315 --> 01:21:59,600
Bobby was the last one.
I'm just gonna be an old maid.

730
01:21:59,860 --> 01:22:03,644
That's just the way it goes.
You win a few, you lose a few.

731
01:22:03,905 --> 01:22:04,985
What do you do?

732
01:22:05,198 --> 01:22:07,654
Nothing's ever the way it's supposed to be.

733
01:22:07,868 --> 01:22:09,362
You're right. Come on.

734
01:22:13,122 --> 01:22:17,250
I want to tell you something.
What I've done hasn't worked out well.

735
01:22:17,460 --> 01:22:21,327
I think maybe we better think
of something else for you.

736
01:22:23,090 --> 01:22:26,423
I guess Ruth Popper's got
about as good a setup as anyone.

737
01:22:26,635 --> 01:22:30,467
Why, sure. Sonny's reasonably
good-looking and he's young.

738
01:22:30,722 --> 01:22:33,889
Don't you know?
It's been going on about six months.

739
01:22:34,100 --> 01:22:36,935
- I thought you kids knew everything.
- That's silly!

740
01:22:37,145 --> 01:22:38,390
She's 40 years old.

741
01:22:38,604 --> 01:22:41,274
So am I, honey.
It's kind of an itchy age.

742
01:22:41,524 --> 01:22:43,066
Want an orange?

743
01:22:43,317 --> 01:22:45,025
I don't believe it.

744
01:22:45,736 --> 01:22:48,488
Sonny's always wanted to go with me.

745
01:22:53,827 --> 01:22:55,950
Pretty easy shot, sheriff.

746
01:23:04,670 --> 01:23:06,081
Sheriff, we got trouble.

747
01:23:08,090 --> 01:23:11,174
Goddamn you, Monroe!
You made me scratch.

748
01:23:11,385 --> 01:23:15,299
Sorry, sheriff, but Johnny Clarg's
little girl's been kidnapped.

749
01:23:15,681 --> 01:23:18,847
The preacher's boy
put her in his car two hours ago.

750
01:23:19,142 --> 01:23:23,140
What the hell? Maybe Joe Bob
just give her a ride home.

751
01:23:23,354 --> 01:23:25,928
Be doing her a favour in this hot weather.

752
01:23:26,149 --> 01:23:28,818
Who'd want to kidnap Molly Clarg?

753
01:23:29,026 --> 01:23:30,686
I just know she's not home.

754
01:23:30,903 --> 01:23:33,441
They was seen headed toward Olney.

755
01:23:33,656 --> 01:23:36,277
Mrs. Clarg's afraid that Joe Bob might be...

756
01:23:36,533 --> 01:23:39,736
Gonna molest her or something.

757
01:23:39,953 --> 01:23:41,910
You and these boys come with us.

758
01:23:42,622 --> 01:23:45,789
If that's the way it is, no telling what we'll find.

759
01:24:12,400 --> 01:24:13,859
Molly!

760
01:24:18,823 --> 01:24:20,899
Get him! Ain't you going to?

761
01:24:21,409 --> 01:24:22,737
Here's my little girl.

762
01:24:22,952 --> 01:24:25,822
He's the one that done it.
Why don't you get him?

763
01:24:26,038 --> 01:24:28,873
If my husband was here, he'd kill him dead.

764
01:24:34,462 --> 01:24:37,582
What'd you do to that child?
We know you done something.

765
01:24:37,882 --> 01:24:39,163
Come on.

766
01:24:42,011 --> 01:24:43,291
Filthy!

767
01:24:43,512 --> 01:24:47,344
Here now, grab her.
None of this goddamn frenzy.

768
01:24:51,645 --> 01:24:53,388
It's the Lord's justice, son.

769
01:24:53,605 --> 01:24:56,226
You'll suffer with the murderer and the thief.

770
01:24:56,441 --> 01:25:00,308
Sonny, drive that Plymouth to town.
We gotta get this man to jail.

771
01:25:10,204 --> 01:25:12,991
- Doctor said he did nothing.
- Never had the guts.

772
01:25:13,207 --> 01:25:16,576
- Preacher's boy.
- Sheriff figured he done something.

773
01:25:23,383 --> 01:25:26,253
Isn't it terrible, Sonny?
Did you see anything?

774
01:25:26,511 --> 01:25:28,669
Nothing to see except Mrs. Clarg.

775
01:25:28,888 --> 01:25:31,426
If she had a gun, she might've killed us all.

776
01:25:31,682 --> 01:25:33,176
Joe Bob didn't do nothing.

777
01:25:33,392 --> 01:25:36,726
He must've done something.
It scares me to death.

778
01:25:36,937 --> 01:25:40,353
You never can tell when something
terrible is gonna happen.

779
01:25:41,608 --> 01:25:43,517
It's okay. They got him now.

780
01:25:43,777 --> 01:25:45,568
I called you before.

781
01:25:46,529 --> 01:25:47,525
You did?

782
01:25:48,490 --> 01:25:52,108
I felt lonesome. Thought you might
want to drive around.

783
01:25:55,538 --> 01:25:57,910
Well, I'm supposed to be someplace.

784
01:25:58,165 --> 01:26:01,997
I'm still a little scared.
Please take me riding.

785
01:26:07,799 --> 01:26:09,128
Where will we drive?

786
01:26:36,201 --> 01:26:37,446
Ever hear from Duane?

787
01:26:37,660 --> 01:26:38,858
Got a postcard.

788
01:26:39,245 --> 01:26:41,783
I really feel sad about that.

789
01:26:42,206 --> 01:26:45,622
He makes 320 a month.
Said he bought a car.

790
01:26:46,627 --> 01:26:51,004
I'll always be a little in love with Duane.
We had too much against us.

791
01:26:51,882 --> 01:26:54,503
It wasn't easy being the one to break up.

792
01:27:24,162 --> 01:27:26,368
- Sonny?
- What?

793
01:28:21,924 --> 01:28:23,715
Not here.

794
01:28:23,926 --> 01:28:26,843
I'm too old for screwing in cars.

795
01:28:30,098 --> 01:28:32,055
I don't like to hurry.

796
01:28:32,851 --> 01:28:36,635
Why don't we go to Wichita
and get a motel room?

797
01:28:36,980 --> 01:28:39,305
I'm afraid to. My folks are watching me.

798
01:28:39,524 --> 01:28:41,931
They know I don't want to go to college.

799
01:28:42,151 --> 01:28:44,856
They might think we'll run off
and get married.

800
01:28:46,697 --> 01:28:48,939
We'll do it when it's safe.

801
01:28:49,742 --> 01:28:52,149
We got all summer.

802
01:29:45,001 --> 01:29:47,124
- Hey, Duane.
- Hey, buddy!

803
01:29:48,672 --> 01:29:49,916
You turned roughneck.

804
01:29:50,131 --> 01:29:52,704
Had to so I could keep the pool hall open.

805
01:29:52,926 --> 01:29:54,752
- When did you get in?
- About 2:00.

806
01:29:54,969 --> 01:29:56,796
I thought I'd surprise you.

807
01:29:58,472 --> 01:29:59,504
Is this yours?

808
01:29:59,723 --> 01:30:03,258
How about that?
38, 000 miles and she runs like new.

809
01:30:03,477 --> 01:30:05,304
- Do you want a beer?
- Not me.

810
01:30:05,896 --> 01:30:08,268
That's all I eat for breakfast anymore.

811
01:30:08,482 --> 01:30:10,474
Hey, sure is a nice car.

812
01:30:10,734 --> 01:30:14,601
I like to drive it so much, I thought
I'd drop home for the weekend.

813
01:30:16,489 --> 01:30:19,573
You can't take too good care
of a car like this.

814
01:30:20,701 --> 01:30:22,493
I wash her every week.

815
01:30:22,703 --> 01:30:24,162
It looks great.

816
01:30:24,997 --> 01:30:26,028
Hear about Joe Bob?

817
01:30:26,290 --> 01:30:28,578
I always knew he was crazy.

818
01:30:28,834 --> 01:30:32,534
He didn't do nothing, except get her
to take her underpants off.

819
01:30:33,171 --> 01:30:34,796
He's out of jail now.

820
01:30:35,882 --> 01:30:37,875
You still screwing that old lady?

821
01:30:39,177 --> 01:30:41,846
No. Yeah.
I've been kind of busy.

822
01:30:42,555 --> 01:30:44,797
I seen old Leroy last week.

823
01:30:45,099 --> 01:30:47,672
He thought you and Jacy been going together.

824
01:30:48,310 --> 01:30:49,686
Yeah, we have, a little.

825
01:30:49,895 --> 01:30:53,346
She's been bored, so sometimes
we go eat Mexican food.

826
01:30:53,649 --> 01:30:55,937
I hear that ain't all you been eating.

827
01:30:57,069 --> 01:31:00,318
Whoever told you that don't know
what he's talking about.

828
01:31:00,530 --> 01:31:02,404
I been going with her. Why not?

829
01:31:02,615 --> 01:31:05,616
I never said I blamed you for it. I don't much.

830
01:31:05,952 --> 01:31:08,703
I never thought you'd do that.
We was friends.

831
01:31:08,913 --> 01:31:12,282
We are. What you so mad for?
I never done nothing to you.

832
01:31:12,500 --> 01:31:15,037
- Screwing my girl ain't nothing?
- I ain't.

833
01:31:15,252 --> 01:31:17,743
- Hell, you ain't!
- Well, I ain't.

834
01:31:18,005 --> 01:31:19,665
- She's not your girl.
- She is!

835
01:31:19,881 --> 01:31:22,918
- You don't live here no more.
- That makes no difference!

836
01:31:23,134 --> 01:31:26,420
I'm getting her back.
She'll marry me someday.

837
01:31:26,638 --> 01:31:28,844
- She won't.
- We're meant to get married.

838
01:31:29,057 --> 01:31:30,551
She's off to college soon.

839
01:31:30,767 --> 01:31:34,100
I doubt I'll get to go with her
myself, once she gets off.

840
01:31:34,312 --> 01:31:37,312
I didn't think it could hurt
to go with her this summer.

841
01:31:37,523 --> 01:31:40,061
- She'll never marry you.
- Don't tell me she won't!

842
01:31:40,984 --> 01:31:45,776
She'd never let you screw her.
I was just seeing how honest you was.

843
01:31:46,031 --> 01:31:49,197
Jacy'd never let you.
You ain't that good a cocksman.

844
01:31:49,993 --> 01:31:52,662
You never even screwed Charlene
all that time.

845
01:31:52,871 --> 01:31:55,112
Course I didn't! You know why?

846
01:31:55,331 --> 01:31:58,451
Because you had the pickup
all the time Saturday night.

847
01:31:58,668 --> 01:32:00,375
I didn't have time to screw her.

848
01:32:00,586 --> 01:32:03,456
I could've done it in five minutes
without a pickup.

849
01:32:03,839 --> 01:32:07,006
She only went with you because
you was in the backfield...

850
01:32:07,259 --> 01:32:11,043
- ... and I was in the line.
- What are you saying? We was in love.

851
01:32:11,263 --> 01:32:14,429
You was. She likes me as much
as she ever liked you.

852
01:32:14,724 --> 01:32:17,511
- That's a lie.
- I'll stay with her all night too.

853
01:32:17,727 --> 01:32:19,186
- She promised.
- You won't.

854
01:32:19,395 --> 01:32:20,510
Why shouldn't I?

855
01:32:20,730 --> 01:32:24,264
She told me you couldn't do it
that time in Wichita Falls.

856
01:32:47,254 --> 01:32:48,665
What happened?

857
01:32:53,719 --> 01:32:56,803
This is your Turntable Matinee on KTRN...

858
01:32:57,014 --> 01:33:01,640
...where you can hear Fulton Lewis Jr.
every Monday through Friday, 6:00 p.m.

859
01:33:01,851 --> 01:33:04,058
Now here's Hank Williams.

860
01:33:05,104 --> 01:33:08,224
There's a lady in the waiting room.
She sent you this.

861
01:33:20,994 --> 01:33:22,738
Could you tell her I'm asleep?

862
01:33:23,413 --> 01:33:24,693
Please?

863
01:33:24,956 --> 01:33:26,285
All right.

864
01:33:52,607 --> 01:33:53,805
That too cold?

865
01:33:54,025 --> 01:33:55,567
No, it's great.

866
01:33:57,403 --> 01:34:00,108
Say, I hear Duane joined the Army.

867
01:34:00,364 --> 01:34:02,321
Good place for him too.

868
01:34:02,575 --> 01:34:04,982
He didn't mean to hit me with the bottle.

869
01:34:05,202 --> 01:34:07,954
That boy's always had meanness in him.

870
01:34:08,538 --> 01:34:11,990
Jacy's the kind of girl that
brings out the meanness in a man.

871
01:34:12,209 --> 01:34:14,118
She's just like her grandmother.

872
01:34:16,796 --> 01:34:20,461
I hadn't ought to talk about them.
We was all good friends once.

873
01:34:21,551 --> 01:34:23,839
Dan roughnecked with Gene Farrow.

874
01:34:24,720 --> 01:34:27,472
He and Lois used to live in this one-room place...

875
01:34:27,723 --> 01:34:29,550
...over the newspaper office.

876
01:34:29,975 --> 01:34:33,723
Lois couldn't afford a flour sack, much less a mink.

877
01:34:36,022 --> 01:34:39,023
I've always had a soft spot for her, though.

878
01:34:41,319 --> 01:34:44,189
I wondered a lot of times
what would've happened...

879
01:34:44,447 --> 01:34:47,116
...if my Dan had made
the strikes that Gene made.

880
01:34:47,325 --> 01:34:49,815
They offered that rig to him first.

881
01:34:53,789 --> 01:34:56,825
Dan Morgan never took a chance in his life.

882
01:34:57,793 --> 01:34:59,501
Do you wish y'all had made it?

883
01:35:03,506 --> 01:35:06,080
Sure, I wish we'd made it.

884
01:35:08,469 --> 01:35:11,920
I guess the Army won't take me
now I just got one good eye.

885
01:35:12,139 --> 01:35:14,428
You want to go to Korea and get killed?

886
01:35:14,683 --> 01:35:18,930
You ain't got your senses back yet,
what few you ever had.

887
01:35:20,355 --> 01:35:22,811
The café won't run itself. You rest up now.

888
01:35:23,025 --> 01:35:25,266
Here's for the cheeseburger.

889
01:35:25,527 --> 01:35:28,278
I'll bring your change when I bring your supper.

890
01:35:59,976 --> 01:36:01,434
Come on in.

891
01:36:10,152 --> 01:36:12,228
I was so worried. I had to see you.

892
01:36:12,446 --> 01:36:14,105
I've been missing you.

893
01:36:14,364 --> 01:36:17,400
And I'm a lot better than I was. Here, sit down.

894
01:36:17,909 --> 01:36:21,741
You can't believe how famous we are.
We're all anyone talks about.

895
01:36:21,954 --> 01:36:24,410
- Yeah, I guess so.
- I want us to get married.

896
01:36:25,166 --> 01:36:27,123
- What?
- I really do.

897
01:36:27,376 --> 01:36:29,867
- Get married?
- Just as soon as you want to.

898
01:36:30,087 --> 01:36:32,792
- Don't you want to?
- Oh, yeah.

899
01:36:33,382 --> 01:36:36,750
The town will be knocked for a loop.
They'll never forget it.

900
01:36:36,968 --> 01:36:38,462
Ain't you going to college?

901
01:36:38,678 --> 01:36:42,177
I don't care about that.
I love you. That's more important.

902
01:36:43,182 --> 01:36:47,310
You were so dear to fight for me.
My folks won't like it but we'll run off.

903
01:36:47,520 --> 01:36:49,311
- They'll kill us.
- No, they won't.

904
01:36:49,522 --> 01:36:51,431
- They'll kill me.
- They'll get over it.

905
01:36:51,649 --> 01:36:53,475
You work for Daddy now anyway.

906
01:36:53,692 --> 01:36:56,812
Pretty soon, they'll love you
just as much as I do.

907
01:36:59,614 --> 01:37:01,025
Can we?

908
01:37:01,658 --> 01:37:04,742
Sure, I just hope I can see to drive.

909
01:37:05,120 --> 01:37:07,326
Don't you worry. I can drive.

910
01:37:17,590 --> 01:37:19,297
Don't do that, Sonny.

911
01:37:19,716 --> 01:37:21,175
Why not?

912
01:37:21,426 --> 01:37:23,668
We're man and wife. We can do anything.

913
01:37:23,887 --> 01:37:26,592
Not while I'm driving. I might have a wreck.

914
01:37:27,140 --> 01:37:31,303
Wouldn't it be awful if Mama
and Daddy got the police after us?

915
01:37:31,561 --> 01:37:35,689
- They don't even know where we are.
- I had to leave them a note.

916
01:37:35,898 --> 01:37:39,481
- So they wouldn't worry.
- You shouldn't have done that.

917
01:37:39,693 --> 01:37:42,065
I figured they'd have to know sometime.

918
01:37:42,279 --> 01:37:44,485
Well, what could they get us for?

919
01:37:44,698 --> 01:37:47,568
We got a right to get married.
Ain't we?

920
01:37:47,909 --> 01:37:49,653
I guess so.

921
01:37:52,872 --> 01:37:56,739
I wish you didn't have that
stupid eye patch. It's really creepy.

922
01:37:56,959 --> 01:37:59,118
I can take it off pretty soon.

923
01:38:00,046 --> 01:38:04,542
About two hours will be Lake Texoma.
Have a room to ourself.

924
01:38:04,800 --> 01:38:08,335
My goodness. You're sitting so close,
I can barely drive.

925
01:38:35,329 --> 01:38:36,609
Oh, goodness.

926
01:39:00,018 --> 01:39:00,884
Howdy.

927
01:39:01,103 --> 01:39:03,428
- What part of Texas y'all from?
- Anarene.

928
01:39:03,647 --> 01:39:05,438
Newlyweds, ain't you?

929
01:39:06,024 --> 01:39:09,439
Y'all better follow me in.
Somebody's looking for you.

930
01:39:09,652 --> 01:39:12,487
We got a right to get married.
How can you arrest us?

931
01:39:12,863 --> 01:39:16,030
I ain't arresting you.
I just want you to come with me.

932
01:39:16,242 --> 01:39:19,907
- I don't know what your rights are.
- I guess we better follow him.

933
01:39:20,120 --> 01:39:23,370
I'll just be heartbroken
if my folks have done this.

934
01:39:28,128 --> 01:39:31,164
You think I worked hard
so Jacy'd end up in a pool hall?

935
01:39:31,589 --> 01:39:34,080
- We was gonna get an apartment.
- I'll bet!

936
01:39:34,300 --> 01:39:37,883
Where are your car keys, hon?
It's a hell of a note!

937
01:39:38,095 --> 01:39:40,764
- Shut up and take her home.
- You bet I will!

938
01:39:40,973 --> 01:39:44,555
You take her car.
As far as I'm concerned, he can walk!

939
01:40:13,128 --> 01:40:16,082
Not much of a wedding night, huh?

940
01:40:16,339 --> 01:40:17,370
Not much of one.

941
01:40:17,590 --> 01:40:21,042
Here. Have a little drink of bourbon.
It'll pick you up.

942
01:40:21,261 --> 01:40:23,300
Take all of it. I'm gonna drive.

943
01:40:25,765 --> 01:40:27,140
You won't believe this...

944
01:40:27,391 --> 01:40:30,641
...but you're lucky we got you
clear of her quick as we did.

945
01:40:31,020 --> 01:40:34,104
You'd have been better off
staying with Ruth Popper.

946
01:40:34,314 --> 01:40:36,473
Does everybody know about that?

947
01:40:36,733 --> 01:40:37,931
Of course.

948
01:40:38,443 --> 01:40:42,772
Sounded like a good deal to me, kiddo.
Shouldn't let Jacy turn your head.

949
01:40:43,031 --> 01:40:45,023
Well, she's prettier.

950
01:40:45,950 --> 01:40:50,161
I guess I shouldn't have, though.
I guess I treated her terrible.

951
01:40:50,413 --> 01:40:51,823
Guess you did.

952
01:41:11,849 --> 01:41:13,972
Sure weren't out of Texas very long.

953
01:41:14,185 --> 01:41:17,139
Oklahoma's not much of an improvement.

954
01:41:22,568 --> 01:41:24,441
It's not the same now.

955
01:41:26,196 --> 01:41:29,280
Nothing's really been right since Sam the Lion died.

956
01:41:34,912 --> 01:41:36,786
No, it hasn't.

957
01:41:40,459 --> 01:41:42,037
Oh, God.

958
01:41:44,963 --> 01:41:47,668
I get sad if I think of Sam for long.

959
01:41:51,595 --> 01:41:53,671
Did you know he had beautiful hands?

960
01:41:55,473 --> 01:41:57,762
I guess you liked him, didn't you?

961
01:41:58,935 --> 01:42:01,011
I guess everybody did.

962
01:42:03,105 --> 01:42:06,391
Well, I'll tell you, it was different with me.

963
01:42:06,734 --> 01:42:08,144
I loved him.

964
01:42:09,778 --> 01:42:11,735
He loved me too.

965
01:42:17,369 --> 01:42:21,117
Are you the one he used to take
swimming out at the tank?

966
01:42:21,331 --> 01:42:23,537
He told you about that, huh?

967
01:42:24,750 --> 01:42:26,293
Yeah, I was the one.

968
01:42:29,880 --> 01:42:32,751
I guess if it wasn't for Sam...

969
01:42:32,966 --> 01:42:36,501
...I'd just about have missed it. Whatever it is.

970
01:42:38,138 --> 01:42:41,423
I'd have been one of them amity types that thinks...

971
01:42:41,683 --> 01:42:45,348
...that playing bridge is
the best thing that life has to offer.

972
01:42:53,110 --> 01:42:55,186
Old Sam the Lion.

973
01:42:58,157 --> 01:43:02,284
Nobody knows where he got that name.
I gave it to him.

974
01:43:02,953 --> 01:43:04,281
One night...

975
01:43:04,746 --> 01:43:07,035
...it just came to me.

976
01:43:11,252 --> 01:43:13,292
He was so pleased.

977
01:43:16,799 --> 01:43:19,254
I was 22 years old then.

978
01:43:20,636 --> 01:43:22,178
Can you imagine?

979
01:43:26,391 --> 01:43:27,554
It's terrible...

980
01:43:27,767 --> 01:43:31,682
...to only meet one man in life
who knows what you're worth.

981
01:43:33,398 --> 01:43:34,477
Just terrible.

982
01:43:37,693 --> 01:43:39,187
I've looked too.

983
01:43:40,946 --> 01:43:43,354
You wouldn't believe how I've looked.

984
01:43:48,120 --> 01:43:51,286
Well, now I know. That's why Sam liked you.

985
01:43:51,498 --> 01:43:52,529
Loved me.

986
01:43:52,749 --> 01:43:54,243
