1001
01:45:20,664 --> 01:45:21,743
You don't mean it.

1002
01:45:21,999 --> 01:45:25,202
Seems longer than that
since you and Duane played ball.

1003
01:45:25,460 --> 01:45:27,002
I seen Duane a while ago.

1004
01:45:27,212 --> 01:45:29,584
He's home on leave, wearing his uniform.

1005
01:45:29,839 --> 01:45:31,796
I ain't seen him yet.

1006
01:45:37,221 --> 01:45:39,130
- How are you, Chester?
- Fine, coach.

1007
01:45:39,348 --> 01:45:42,515
See if we can't stretch
that goddamn thing a little.

1008
01:45:42,726 --> 01:45:47,055
You know a man never ought to cheat,
unless it's for a good cause.

1009
01:45:48,190 --> 01:45:50,099
He's a good old boy, ain't he?

1010
01:46:42,782 --> 01:46:44,276
Hi, Mrs. Jackson.

1011
01:46:44,576 --> 01:46:45,607
Duane here?

1012
01:46:45,952 --> 01:46:50,032
That's his car out there, ain't it?
He's here if he ain't walked off.

1013
01:46:58,047 --> 01:46:59,541
Hi, how you been?

1014
01:47:00,090 --> 01:47:01,632
Pretty good.

1015
01:47:04,219 --> 01:47:06,971
I been thinking all week that I'd run into you.

1016
01:47:09,682 --> 01:47:11,509
I heard you was going to Korea.

1017
01:47:11,726 --> 01:47:14,643
Thought I'd get over
and see you before you got off.

1018
01:47:15,646 --> 01:47:18,766
Glad you did.
I'm taking the bus in the morning.

1019
01:47:26,448 --> 01:47:29,947
Want to go to the picture show?
Miss Mosey has to close it.

1020
01:47:30,160 --> 01:47:33,576
- Tonight's the last night.
- Yeah, might as well go.

1021
01:47:33,830 --> 01:47:36,784
Hate to miss the last night. Take the Mercury.

1022
01:47:37,166 --> 01:47:39,622
Be my last chance to drive it for a while.

1023
01:47:46,008 --> 01:47:48,463
- Ready, Matthew?
- All ready.

1024
01:48:14,451 --> 01:48:16,360
Take them to Missouri, Matt.

1025
01:49:15,883 --> 01:49:17,377
That was a good movie.

1026
01:49:17,593 --> 01:49:19,550
Seen it here before once.

1027
01:49:20,721 --> 01:49:23,342
Let's run over to Wichita and drink some beer.

1028
01:49:23,557 --> 01:49:25,965
Okay. I got lots of time till morning.

1029
01:49:26,226 --> 01:49:27,471
Sure.

1030
01:49:29,312 --> 01:49:31,982
- So long.
- Sorry you're closing the show.

1031
01:49:32,190 --> 01:49:34,728
Nobody wants to come to shows no more.

1032
01:49:35,193 --> 01:49:38,858
Kid baseball in the summer, television all the time.

1033
01:49:40,448 --> 01:49:43,863
Sam had lived, I believe we could've kept it going.

1034
01:49:44,368 --> 01:49:46,906
But I just didn't have the know-how.

1035
01:49:48,038 --> 01:49:51,288
Won't be much to do in town
with the picture show closed.

1036
01:49:53,835 --> 01:49:55,413
Well, so long.

1037
01:49:56,171 --> 01:49:57,202
Duane.

1038
01:49:58,465 --> 01:50:00,504
You watch out now, overseas.

1039
01:50:23,655 --> 01:50:25,694
Sure weren't no women around.

1040
01:50:28,618 --> 01:50:31,535
I guess the next piece of ass I get will be yellow.

1041
01:50:32,288 --> 01:50:34,079
I wish I was going with you.

1042
01:50:36,583 --> 01:50:38,410
Take care of the car for me.

1043
01:50:38,961 --> 01:50:40,419
Your ma don't need it?

1044
01:50:40,629 --> 01:50:43,748
I wouldn't want her driving it, the way she drives.

1045
01:50:43,965 --> 01:50:46,919
You might help her take
the groceries home sometimes.

1046
01:51:00,147 --> 01:51:01,475
You ever...

1047
01:51:01,732 --> 01:51:03,142
You ever hear from Jacy?

1048
01:51:04,026 --> 01:51:05,852
No, not a thing.

1049
01:51:06,111 --> 01:51:10,155
She don't get home much.
Ain't been back to town since August.

1050
01:51:10,365 --> 01:51:12,357
I guess she always stays in Dallas.

1051
01:51:13,076 --> 01:51:14,867
Yeah, probably does.

1052
01:51:16,370 --> 01:51:18,363
I guess there's lots to do there.

1053
01:51:24,128 --> 01:51:26,334
I ain't over her yet, you know.

1054
01:51:28,507 --> 01:51:30,416
No, I ain't over her yet.

1055
01:51:31,760 --> 01:51:33,503
It's the damnedest thing.

1056
01:51:36,681 --> 01:51:41,224
That's the only reason you and I
got into it that time, you know.

1057
01:51:43,938 --> 01:51:45,396
Reckon she likes Dallas?

1058
01:51:46,357 --> 01:51:48,017
Hard to say. Maybe she does.

1059
01:51:51,528 --> 01:51:55,739
Reckon you and her would've got it
straighted out if I hadn't butted in?

1060
01:51:58,952 --> 01:52:01,787
No, they'd have annulled me too,
even if we had.

1061
01:52:07,168 --> 01:52:09,659
